If you want to do work on jupyter notebook first download jupyter notebook by typing command
 pip3 install jupyter -y (with root user)
 
After changing user from root to normal
1) type cd
2) vi .bashrc (in linux)

export HADOOP_HOME=/home/adhoc/Desktop/hadoop2/hadoop-2.7.3
export HADOOP_INSTALL=$HADOOP_HOME
export HADOOP_MAPRED_HOME=$HADOOP_HOME
export HADOOP_COMMON_HOME=$HADOOP_HOME
export HADOOP_HDFS_HOME=$HADOOP_HOME
export YARN_HOME=$HADOOP_HOME
export HADOOP_COMMON_LIB_NATIVE_DIR=$HADOOP_HOME/lib/native
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/java/jdk1.8.0
PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$HADOOP_HOME/bin:$HADOOP_HOME/sbin:$PATH
export PATH
export SPARK_HOME=/home/adhoc/Desktop/spark-2.4.4-bin-hadoop2.7 ####### HERE YOU HAVE TO WRITE PATH OF UNTAR SPARK FILE
export PYSPARK_PYTHON=python3
export PATH=$PATH:/home/adhoc/Desktop/spark-2.4.4-bin-hadoop2.7/bin

export PYSPARK_DRIVER_PYTHON=jupyter         ( Do this if you want to work on jupyter notebook Else skip these two lines)
export PYSPARK_DRIVER_PYTHON_OPTS='notebook'

###################################################################################################################################

AFTER DOING THIS CHANGES DONT FORGET TO TYPE "source .bashrc" and dont do  all these changes in root user
now you can type pyspark it will automatically redirected you to jupyter notebook 
